20/11/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Office of the High Representative (OHR) and British Ambassador to BiH Matthew Rycroft -- whose country currently holds the rotating EU presidency -- issued a joint call Friday (18 November) for the speedy adoption of a new, state-level law on higher education that would be in line with European standards.
In separate statements, the OHR and Rycroft welcomed the establishment of a task force responsible for drafting the new legislation by 9 December.
The British EU presidency has listed reform of the BiH higher educational sector as a top priority.
(Fena, OHR Sources - 18/11/05)
